commit.message: Fixed the speeeding-up-animation bug that occured with multiple calls of okay-lucy
Added Text-To-Speech response for invalid intents. Updated the API.AI account to the new group account.

1. Added Lucy icon trigger of turning on the microphone 2. manually animated the Lucy icon by breaking down the gif into png frame and looping through them. This indicates that “Okay Lucy” has been called and will be listening for query for 6 seconds (or refreshes for 10 seconds if a newer query is made) 3. fixed initialization scheme for audio scheme so the page redirects to options page and back to main page if already permissions are given. There were ALOT of tricky corner cases since you actually can’t check if you have getUserMedia permissions directly from background.js - I’ll explain later. 4. initialize.html how has instructions on how the audio channel permissions process works. 5. Call to “Okay Lucy” more robust by using regex 6. Updated the website navigation list in parse.js
